definitions.definition: To make a path in, or on (something), or for (someone).
To navigate through a file system directory tree (to a desired file or folder).
examples: Next, you need to path to the location of the executable and run it from there.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To make a path in, or on (something), or for (someone).
secondary_definitions: ( computing , intransitive ) To navigate through a file system directory tree (to a desired file or folder).
